#: ../../../reference/generated/numpy.logaddexp2.rst:4
msgid "numpy.logaddexp2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:2
msgid "Logarithm of the sum of exponentiations of the inputs in base-2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:4
msgid ""
"Calculates ``log2(2**x1 + 2**x2)``. This function is useful in machine "
"learning when the calculated probabilities of events may be so small as to "
"exceed the range of normal floating point numbers.  In such cases the base-2 "
"logarithm of the calculated probability can be used instead. This function "
"allows adding probabilities stored in such a fashion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:15
msgid "**x1, x2**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:-1
msgid "array_like"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:13
msgid ""
"Input values. If ``x1.shape != x2.shape``, they must be broadcastable to a "
"common shape (which becomes the shape of the output)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:21
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:-1
msgid "ndarray, None, or tuple of ndarray and None, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:18
msgid ""
"A location into which the result is stored. If provided, it must have a "
"shape that the inputs broadcast to. If not provided or None, a freshly-"
"allocated array is returned. A tuple (possible only as a keyword argument) "
"must have length equal to the number of outputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:29
msgid "**where**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:-1
msgid "array_like, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.logaddexp2:24
msgid ""
"This condition is broadcast over the input. At locations where the condition "
"is True, the `out` array will be set to the ufunc result. Elsewhere, the "
"`out` array will retain its original value. Note that if an uninitialized "
"`out` array is created via the default ``out=None``, locations within it "
"where the condition is False will remain uninitialized."
msgstr ""

